fy these interactions to ensure things operate smoothly for the user.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Analyzing port registration issues**\\\\n\\\\nI’m considering how `registerKnownPorts` adds ports for both serial and parallel during static initialization, but these might get duplicated as `getPortIdentifiers` runs. Testing should check that the first identifier has the expected name and type. It seems necessary to call `registerKnownPorts` for both serial and parallel to ensure they’re added correctly. However, there are potential complications with JNI callbacks in Native Image when accessing metadata. I’ll need to clarify if additional configurations are needed.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_xYXZzoDFawby71ApO7X6pxA6|fc_0f7bc8181a2299f00169f7138dff8881a3a8bad788509da80d\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.rxtx/rxtx/2.1.7/src/test/native/rxtxSerialStub.c\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"JNIEXPORT jboolean JNICALL Java_gnu_io_RXTXCommDriver_registerKnownPorts(JNIEnv *env, jobject driver, jint portType) {\\n    (void) env;\\n    (void) driver;\\n    (void) portType;\\n    return JNI_TRUE;\\n}\\n\", \"newText\": \"JNIEXPORT jboolean JNICALL Java_gnu_io_RXTXCommDriver_registerKnownPorts(JNIEnv *env, jobject driver, jint portType) {\\n    jclass commPortIdentifier = (*env)->FindClass(env, \\\"gnu/io/CommPortIdentifier\\\");\\n    jmethodID addPortName = (*env)->GetStaticMethodID(\\n            env,\\n            commPortIdentifier,\\n            \\\"addPortName\\\",\\n            \\\"(Ljava/lang/String;ILgnu/io/CommDriver;)V\\\");\\n    const char *portName = portType == 1 ? \\\"rxtx-stub-serial\\\" : \\\"rxtx-stub-parallel\\\";\\n    jstring javaPortName = (*env)->NewStringUTF(env, portName);\\n    (*env)->CallStaticVoidMethod(env, commPortIdentifier, addPortName, javaPortName, portType, driver);\\n    return JNI_TRUE;\\n}\\n\"}]}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"mode